Title: How do I do a not equal in a Laravel Eloquent query?
Body: <p>In Laravel Eloquent queries, I know I can use comparison operators like <code>&gt;</code> and <code>&lt;</code>, but how do I do a <strong>not equals</strong>? I want to filter out using a not equals. For example, for</p>
<pre><code>Model:
    bool a;
    int x;
</code></pre>
<p>I want to do something like:</p>
<pre><code>$results = Model::where('a', true)->where('x' != 5)->get();
</code></pre>
