Title: How to combine multiple Eloquent query results in Laravel?
Body: <p>I’m building search for a Laravel site and I need to search across three different models. I want to paginate the combined results with a generic list view, but I have to merge three query results into one.</p>
<p>How can I do that? I tried this:</p>
<pre><code>$resultList = [];
$pageList = Page::where(function ($q) use ($cleanedSearchTerm) {
    $q-&gt;where('title', 'like', "%{$cleanedSearchTerm}%")
      -&gt;orWhere('body', 'like', "%{$cleanedSearchTerm}%");
});
$articleList = Article::where(function ($q) use ($cleanedSearchTerm) {
    $q-&gt;where('title', 'like', "%{$cleanedSearchTerm}%")
      -&gt;orWhere('body', 'like', "%{$cleanedSearchTerm}%")
      -&gt;orWhere('tags', 'like', "%{$cleanedSearchTerm}%");
});
$postList = Post::where(function ($q) use ($cleanedSearchTerm) {
    $q-&gt;where('title', 'like', "%{$cleanedSearchTerm}%")
      -&gt;orWhere('body', 'like', "%{$cleanedSearchTerm}%")
      -&gt;orWhere('tags', 'like', "%{$cleanedSearchTerm}%");
});

foreach ($pageList as $x) {
    $resultList[] = $x;
}
foreach ($articleList as $x) {
    $resultList[] = $x;
}
foreach ($postList as $x) {
    $resultList[] = $x;
}

return view('search.result_list', [
    'result' =&gt; $resultList,
    'search_term' =&gt; $searchTerm,
]);
</code></pre>
<p>But this doesn’t work. I get an error when I try to paginate the list because it isn’t a paginator/collection.</p>
<p>How can I merge the three lists, <code>$pageList</code>, <code>$articleList</code> and <code>$postList</code>, and paginate the combined results?</p>

